================================================================================

Additional Notice for Research and Academic Use:

This software implements research-grade algorithms for singing voice conversion
optimized for Apple Silicon hardware. If you use this software in academic
research, please consider citing relevant works:

1. RMVPE Algorithm: For robust pitch estimation in singing applications
2. BS-Roformer: For advanced audio source separation
3. Mel-Band Roformer: For audio dereverberation and enhancement

================================================================================

Third-Party Dependencies:

This software uses several third-party libraries and models:

- PyTorch: BSD-style license (https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/master/LICENSE)
- LibROSA: ISC License (https://github.com/librosa/librosa/blob/main/LICENSE.md)
- Audio-separator: MIT License (https://github.com/karaokenerds/python-audio-separator)
- Faiss: MIT License (https://github.com/facebookresearch/faiss/blob/main/LICENSE)

Pre-trained models used:
- BS-Roformer: As per model repository terms
- Mel-Band Roformer: As per model repository terms

Please ensure compliance with all applicable licenses when using this software.

================================================================================

Apple Silicon Optimization Notice:

This software is specifically optimized for Apple Silicon (M1/M2/M3) hardware
and utilizes Apple's Metal Performance Shaders (MPS) framework. The optimizations
are designed to work within Apple's unified memory architecture constraints.

